{"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"variantParse"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"text","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"UnsafePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">!, ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"limit"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"kind":"text","text":"<"},{"text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar"},{"text":">? = nil, ","kind":"text"},{"text":"endptr","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":">?>? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/VariantRef","text":"VariantRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib10VariantRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A single ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is parsed from the content of "},{"code":"text","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The format is described ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"gvariant-text-format.html","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The memory at ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"limit"},{"text":" will never be accessed and the parser behaves as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"if the character at "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"limit"},{"text":" is the nul terminator.  This has the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"effect of bounding ","type":"text"},{"code":"text","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"endptr"},{"text":" is non-","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" then "},{"code":"text","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is permitted to contain data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"following the value that this function parses and "},{"code":"endptr","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"updated to point to the first character past the end of the text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"parsed by this function.  If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"endptr"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" and there is extra data"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"then an error is returned.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"type"},{"type":"text","text":" is non-"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" then the value will be parsed to have that","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"type.  This may result in additional parse errors (in the case that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the parsed value doesn’t fit the type) but may also result in fewer"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"errors (in the case that the type would have been ambiguous, such as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with empty arrays).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In the event that the parsing is successful, the resulting "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"is returned. It is never floating, and must be freed with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Variant.unref"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In case of any error, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":" will be returned.  If ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"error"},{"type":"text","text":" is non-"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"then it will be set to reflect the error that occurred.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Officially, the language understood by the parser is “any string"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"produced by [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Variant.print"},{"type":"text","text":"]”. This explicitly includes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_variant_print()"},{"text":"’s annotated types like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"int64 -1000"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There may be implementation specific restrictions on deeply nested values,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"which would result in a ","type":"text"},{"code":"recursion","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" error. ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Variant","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"guaranteed to handle nesting up to at least 64 levels.","type":"text"}]}],"kind